Compiler Switches
==================

Statements that affect how code is compiled.

Description
	These statements affect how the compiler declares variables,
	arrays and procedures, parses string literals, passes procedure
	parameters and more.

Metacommands
	$DYNAMIC
	$INCLUDE
	$STATIC
	$LANG

Compiler Options
	OPTION BASE
	OPTION BYVAL
	OPTION DYNAMIC
	OPTION ESCAPE
	OPTION EXPLICIT
	OPTION GOSUB
	OPTION NOGOSUB
	OPTION NOKEYWORD
	OPTION PRIVATE
	OPTION STATIC

Set Default Datatypes
	DEFBYTE
	DEFDBL
	DEFINT
	DEFLNG
	DEFLONGINT
	DEFSHORT
	DEFSNG
	DEFSTR
	DEFUBYTE
	DEFUINT
	DEFULONGINT
	DEFUSHORT

Dialect Differences:
	DEFLONGINT available only in the [-lang fblite] dialect.
	OPTION statements are available only in the [-lang fblite] and [-lang qb] dialects only.
